      "span_text": "Although the measured rate of polar auxin transport (about 10 mm per hour) is sufficient to account for auxin transport from the columella to the elongation zone of an Arabidopsis root in about 2 minutesconsistent with the observed onset of differential growth -the same cannot be said of larger roots, such as those of maize, which respond just as rapidly but have 3-4 mm between columella and elongation zone  ."
